                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/113: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-18T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 18, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1250. Your 1778, November 14. War Department is greatly interested in the
                    maintenance of friendly relations with Spain at this time and has expressed the
                    desire to avoid any action which might possibly lead to friction or give rise to
                    an incident. In any discussions you may have, therefore, on the subject of the
                    aviators and their planes, you should bear in mind the War Department’s wishes
                    and carefully refrain from any expression which might prove to be a source of
                    irritation.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier as Dept’s 234.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
